# Use the Reverse DNS to find out the name of the server linked to the 10.51.1.81 IP address

81.1.51.10.in-addr.arpa. 86400	IN	PTR	dpm-master.42.us.org.

# dig +noall +answer -x 10.51.1.81 
# The +noall, +answer combination basically tells dig to only report the answer of the DNS query and skip the rest of the output. -x option to do a reverse DNS lookup
